					<img alt='' src='http://i1.wp.com/a0.twimg.com/profile_images/1121943059/86478453-202b-4d24-9249-af4325c61a16_normal.png?resize=40%2C40' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' />
					<span class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn"><a href='http://twitter.com/_stevemoore' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Steven Moore (@_stevemoore)</a></cite>					</span>

					<a href="http://p2pconnects.us/2013/03/07/the-future-of-trust-in-a-networked-society/comment-page-1/#comment-46" class="comment-date"><time pubdate datetime="2013-05-02T13:59:06+00:00">May 2, 2013 at 1:59 pm</time></a>
					<span class="sep">&middot;</span>
										<span class="sep">&middot;</span>
					<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2013/03/07/the-future-of-trust-in-a-networked-society/?replytocom=46#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-46", "46", "respond", "3")'>Reply</a> &rarr;				</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
							</footer>
			<div class="comment-content"><p>John- I love how Bitcoin has the ability to escrow with 3rd party and a new way of escrow without a party involved built in and will be developed out as trust is built in this new &#8220;synthetic commodity money&#8221; system in the p2p environment&#8230; Checking out Trustcloud right now.</p>
</div>
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->

	<ul class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-p2pconnectsus bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-48">
		<article id="comment-48" class="comment">
			<footer>
				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
					<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2978114801eea14846efda62e01f4f13?s=40&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' />
					<span class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn"><a href='http://p2pconnects.us' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>John Light</a></cite>					</span>

					<a href="http://p2pconnects.us/2013/03/07/the-future-of-trust-in-a-networked-society/comment-page-1/#comment-48" class="comment-date"><time pubdate datetime="2013-05-02T14:15:20+00:00">May 2, 2013 at 2:15 pm</time></a>
					<span class="sep">&middot;</span>
										<span class="sep">&middot;</span>
					<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2013/03/07/the-future-of-trust-in-a-networked-society/?replytocom=48#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-48", "48", "respond", "3")'>Reply</a> &rarr;				</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
							</footer>
			<div class="comment-content"><p>It&#8217;s really is interesting isn&#8217;t it? I&#8217;ve been looking for a 3rd party service that offers reliable escrow for Bitcoin, and right now the options are very limited. Once m-of-n transactions are fully utilized, this centralized escrow business model will be largely unnecessary as the escrow service becomes more decentralized, with more people able to participate. More and more we&#8217;ll rely on services like Trustcloud, Connect.Me, Credport, and Bitcoin-OTC ratings in order to gauge reputation and make decisions about who to trust with short term coin escrow; it will be interesting to see how these systems scale as more people begin using them. Thanks for the comment! </p>
</div>
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->

	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol>

		
	
	
